sql:
SELECT name
FROM companies
ORDER BY name;

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT company_id) AS company_count
FROM company_exchange
WHERE exchange_id = (SELECT exchange_id FROM stock_exchanges WHERE exchange_name = 'ASX');

external_knowledge:
- "giants" refers to companies with the largest market capitalization; 
- "leaders" refers to the CEOs of the companies; 
- "domains" refers to the industries the companies operate in; 
- "stock exchange platforms" refers to the exchanges where the companies are listed; 
- "size" is measured by market capitalization.

